  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2011-04-12",
    "date": "2011-05-17T20:13:24Z",
    "text": "Investment Property Opportunity Act of 2011 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude from gross income gain from the sale of residential real property that is: (1) located in a distressed housing area (i.e., a county with high foreclosure rates and declining housing fair market values), (2) acquired within 18 months after enactment of this Act, and (3) held for more than three years."
